<br>
Three days ago was the 1 yr anniversary of my friends suicide. More like impulsive self-destruction, as he got drunk and drove himself into a metal pole. All over a girl.<br>
<br>
I still feel the loss, and I still think &quot;what if I was there to stop him?&quot; or &quot;Why couldnt someone taken his keys away?&quot; etc etc.<br>
<br>
I understand how you feel. Its a terrible emptiness and despair that gnaws at you. What got me through it, despite my wish to be alone, was forcing myself to go out. I went out and had a good time (well... you know what I mean) in his name. I knew he wanted me to. So I did. And despite wanting to be alone, being with friends him and I had mutually helped alot. Tearful, meaningful reminiscing is wonderful therapy.<br>
<br>
All I can say is dont isolate yourself. Its hard not to, but grief is a communal burden meant to be expressed in a group, not alone. It is unbearable alone. Please, for your own sanity, go out. Socialize. Grieve publicly.<br>
<br>
I dont know what else to say, except...<br>
<br>
/hug<br>
<br>
 <p>-=Aarchus Xhar'Gothe, the Hand of Innoruuk=-

