<br>
I don't know if this helps, but when something like this happened to me it comforted me to know that what I was going through was normal.<br>
<br>
There are, if my training is correct, five different steps in dealing with any major loss, be it from death of the loss of a job. These do not necessarily happen in this order and some might last minutes while others last days/weeks/or years. <br>
<br>
The first stage is Denial. You hinted in that in your last post. 'This cannot be happening' is a typical response.<br>
<br>
The second stage is Anger. You might get angry at the father who you said abused her, or at her, or at yourself. It is natural. &quot;They left me&quot; or &quot;Its all X's fault&quot; are typical responses.<br>
<br>
The third stage is Bargaining. &quot;I'd give anything to have them back&quot; is a typical response. This is seen a lot in people who find out they have a short time to live... friends will say 'If I could take your place I would' or you say 'God if you quit this I'll do X'. Again this is normal<br>
<br>
The fourth stage is Depression. This is the biggie. This is where surrounding yourself with loved ones is almost necessary. They realize the pain you are going through and its ok to just let go.. crying is ok. I had someone tell me once that it was not ok to cry because I was a guy and I needed to be strong. You don't have to be strong. Let your loved ones be strong. But remember at the same time that you must carry on. I could go on on this subject but this is really just an overview.<br>
<br>
The final stage is acceptance. You realize that life does go on and you retain the memories of your friend but move on with your life. <br>
<br>
This is a VERY cursory glance at a horribly complex situation, but I know it helped my a lot. <br>
<br>
Remember you are loved and if you need any help you obviously have many friends here as well as loved ones around you.<br>
<br>
Peace be with you<br>
<br>
Will <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unoirdaila.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Noirdaila</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/02 12:53:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I am so sorry....<br>
